  "role_description": "Site safety manager (HSE Manager) responsible for the overall safety program on industrial construction or refinery projects. Manages safety coordinators, conducts incident investigations, interfaces with client safety representatives, maintains OSHA recordkeeping, manages training programs, oversees permit systems, tracks safety metrics, and reports to project management and corporate HSE.",
  "report_focus": "When structuring this person's reports, look for: safety metrics (TRIR, observations, near-misses), incidents and investigation status, training compliance, permit system performance, audit findings, regulatory compliance issues, client safety concerns, corrective action tracking, and safety program initiatives.",
